he points are probably better spent on Mental Clarity or one of the hp/ac/regen skills.<br><br>On the other hand, it's fun to have and the first time people see it they usually say, &quot;WTF?&quot;. <br><br>It depends on your play style, I guess. I bought it and I'm not sorry but it isn't the most efficient use of AA points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udondorholystorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DondorHolystorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 5:24:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Casting Fury and Paladins</span><hr size=1> You can't crit with &quot;any&quot; dd spell.<br><br>Proc from Tunare sword is 160dd root.  It will not crit proc. <p>"Death smiles at us all, all a man can do is smile back."<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84371" target="_blank">Dondor Holystorm</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umithasbrightblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithas Brightblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/19/02 6:57:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spell Casting Fury and Paladins</span><hr size=1> You get critical blasts with Palladius Axe, at level 1 i get a 106 lifetap.I've also gotten critical heals off a critical blast, turns that 106 nuke to a 212 heal.Healing Adept also changed these taps, with